    - "struct_extra165.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct.__dict__.__contains__ for __init__/__new__ (novel) and struct.error class identity via __eq__ calls and Struct dunder name lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra164.zspec.zsdl — covers struct module-level function __name__.__len__() integer values for all six functions: pack(4)/unpack(6)/calcsize(8)/pack_into(9)/unpack_from(11)/iter_unpack(11) and module lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra163.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.pack/__unpack class names ('builtin_function_or_method') and struct.Struct.__dict__.__contains__ for pack/unpack/size/format/pack_into/iter_unpack/unpack_from and __len__()==16 (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra162.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.pack/__unpack/__pack_into/__unpack_from/__iter_unpack/__calcsize .__name__/__module__ (module-level function identity); pack.__class__.__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra161.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.error/__Struct class identity (__name__/__module__/__bases__) (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra160.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct.__dict__ membership and meta-attributes (__len__()==16/__class__.__name__=='mappingproxy') (table + invariants)."
    - "struct.zspec / early extras — cover struct.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in struct_extra93 through struct_extra165."
    - "Wave 352 theme: struct.Struct class identity via __name__/__module__ and Struct.__dict__ dunder __sizeof__ membership. struct_extra161 anchors struct.Struct.__name__=='Struct' and struct.Struct.__module__=='_struct' as table rows; this spec anchors via __eq__ method call syntax as the primary novel anchor. struct_extra165 anchors __init__ and __new__ as novel dict members; this spec anchors __sizeof__ (also in Struct.__dict__) as an additional novel member. Struct.__name__.__len__()==6 and Struct.__module__.__len__()==7 are first anchors for these integer lengths."
    - "struct.Struct.__dict__.__contains__('__init__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. (Confirmed; struct_extra165 anchors.)"
    - "struct.Struct.__dict__.__contains__('__new__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. (Confirmed; struct_extra165 anchors.)"
    - "struct.Struct.__dict__.__contains__('__sizeof__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. (Novel anchor — struct_extra165 anchors __init__ and __new__ but not __sizeof__.)"
    - "struct.Struct.__name__ == 'Struct'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. struct_extra161 anchors this as a table row."
    - "struct.Struct.__module__ == '_struct'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. struct_extra161 anchors this as a table row."
    - "struct.Struct.__name__.__len__() == 6. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. ('Struct' = 'S'=1+'t'=1+'r'=1+'u'=1+'c'=1+'t'=1 = 6 chars.)"
    - "struct.Struct.__module__.__len__() == 7. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. ('_struct' = '_'=1 + 'struct'=6 = 7 chars.)"
    - "Note: struct.Struct.__dict__ has 16 keys total: __delattr__/__doc__/__getattribute__/__init__/__module__/__new__/__repr__/__setattr__/__sizeof__ (9 dunders) + format/iter_unpack/pack/pack_into/size/unpack/unpack_from (7 non-dunders). struct_extra165 anchors __init__/__new__; this spec adds __sizeof__ as a third novel dunder member anchor."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.__name__ == 'Struct' (6 chars; CamelCase; capital 'S'). struct_extra161 anchors this as a table row; this spec anchors via __eq__ call syntax for a fresh uuiddict166 anchor."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.__module__ == '_struct' (7 chars = '_'=1 + 'struct'=6; private C extension from Modules/_struct.c; the leading underscore marks private C extension; '_struct'(7) > 'Struct'(6) by 1 char — module name is 1 char longer than the class name itself)."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.__name__.__len__() == 6 ('Struct' = 6 chars). This is the first spec to anchor this integer length value. struct_extra161 anchors 'Struct' as a string but not its length."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.__module__.__len__() == 7 ('_struct' = 7 chars). This is the first spec to anchor this integer length value. struct_extra161 anchors '_struct' as a string but not its length."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

